28 Days;;2000;;PG-13;;Comedy,Drama;;6.1;;Betty Thomas;;Sandra Bullock,Viggo Mortensen,Dominic West,Elizabeth Perkins,Azura Skye,Steve Buscemi,Alan Tudyk,Mike O'Malley,Marianne Jean-Baptiste,Reni Santoni,Diane Ladd,Margo Martindale,Susan Krebs,Loudon Wainwright III,Katie Scharf,Meredith Deane,Elizabeth Ruscio,Kathy Payne;;28 days was one of those movies you can tell the writer (Susannah Grant) knows the subject material, maybe even up close and personal. Director (Betty Thomas) did a wonderful job of giving Gwen's (Sandra Bullock) flashbacks that fuzzy look and sound where she isn't sure if they dreamed what happened or if it really did happen.;;https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0191754/